===Etymology===
First attested about 1380. From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|abundaunt}},<ref name=AHD>{{R:American Heritage 1971|page=6}}</ref> {{m|enm|habundaunt}},<ref name=WI3>{{R:MW3 1976|page=8}}</ref> {{m|enm|aboundant}}, from {{etyl|xno|en}} {{m|fro|abundant}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|abondant}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|abundāns}}, present participle of {{m|la|abundo||to overflow, to abound}}. Compare ''[[abound]]''.

